---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import { profile } from "../../data/profile";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="E&O Application Rebuild Case Study | Abhinav Naidu Chintala"
  description="Case study: rebuilding an unstable insurance E&O application into a full-stack Zoho Catalyst workflow with pricing, payments, CRM sync, document generation, and WorkDrive delivery."
>
  <SiteHeader />
  <main class="case-study-page">
    <section class="case-hero">
      <div class="section-shell case-hero-inner">
        <a class="back-link" href="/#work">Back to work</a>
        <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
        <h1>Rebuilding an Insurance E&O Application from the Ground Up</h1>
        <p>
          A solo full-stack rebuild of an unstable Errors & Omissions insurance application,
          delivered in time for policy renewal deadlines and now running real renewals and new business.
        </p>

        <div class="case-meta-grid" aria-label="Case study summary">
          <div>
            <span>Client</span>
            <strong>North American insurance brokerage</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span>Role</span>
            <strong>Solo developer, full-stack</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span>Timeline</span>
            <strong>About 3 weeks</strong>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span>Stack</span>
            <strong>Python, Zoho Catalyst, JavaScript, Webhooks, Zoho CRM, WorkDrive</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-content section-shell">
      <article class="case-section">
        <p class="case-kicker">The Problem</p>
        <h2>An unreliable application was blocking renewals.</h2>
        <p>
          The client had an existing E&O application that was unstable and frequently failed
          mid-workflow, leaving customers stuck and the internal team manually cleaning up broken
          applications. With renewal season approaching, that meant lost business and operational chaos.
        </p>
        <p>
          The brief was a complete rebuild. The difficult part was that the old codebase had no
          documentation, inconsistent naming, and business logic spread across multiple files.
          Renewals and new applications both had to be treated as new business, with dynamic
          premium pricing, strict validation, and kickout conditions for applicants who did not
          meet underwriting criteria.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="case-section">
        <p class="case-kicker">Approach</p>
        <h2>I split the rebuild into three focused phases.</h2>

        <div class="phase-grid">
          <div class="phase-card">
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Multi-step application flow</h3>
            <p>
              Built a 12-step form in vanilla JavaScript, HTML, and CSS with progress saving,
              back-and-forth navigation, mandatory step-level validation, and a unique application
              ID emailed to the user so they could resume later.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-card">
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Pricing and underwriting logic</h3>
            <p>
              Implemented Python-based dynamic premium calculation and kickout rules. Since there
              was no documentation, I reverse-engineered the legacy logic and validated expected
              outcomes with the client.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-card">
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Payment and document pipeline</h3>
            <p>
              Integrated payment links and built a webhook-driven post-payment pipeline that creates
              policy records, syncs Zoho CRM, generates invoices, builds policy documents, stores
              them in WorkDrive, and emails them to the customer.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="case-section case-split">
        <div>
          <p class="case-kicker">Challenges</p>
          <h2>The hardest part was translating insurance rules into software.</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            The insurance domain was the main challenge. Terms like kickout, LA vs CA policy, and
            the rules behind premium adjustments were not intuitive at first. I spent significant
            time clarifying business rules with the client and checking my interpretation against
            expected outcomes.
          </p>
          <p>
            The legacy codebase made this harder. With no documentation and confusing structure, I
            had to separate correct legacy behavior from broken behavior. The project also ran in
            parallel with a US-to-Canada Zoho data-center migration, which added integration work,
            shifting requirements, and deadline pressure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="case-section">
        <p class="case-kicker">Outcome</p>
        <h2>A broken workflow became a production-ready insurance pipeline.</h2>
        <div class="outcome-grid">
          <div>
            <strong>~$250K</strong>
            <span>annual premium revenue now flows through the application</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>0</strong>
            <span>manual recovery steps in the core submission-to-document pipeline</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>End to end</strong>
            <span>form submission, payment, CRM sync, invoice, documents, and email delivery</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Production</strong>
            <span>handling real renewals and new business since launch</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="case-section final-note">
        <p class="case-kicker">What This Shows</p>
        <h2>Fast, high-stakes rebuilds are where I do some of my best work.</h2>
        <p>
          This project shows how I approach undocumented legacy systems, complex business rules,
          and full-stack ownership. I did not just rebuild the frontend or backend in isolation.
          I delivered the full operational path from application start to policy documents delivered.
        </p>
        <a class="button button-primary" href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>Contact me</a>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
